                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.24/730: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-21T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 21, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>384. Your no. 970, June 21, noon. The Department has received information
                    indicating that an attempt is being made to purchase large numbers of used
                    planes for immediate shipment to Spain. We are expecting to receive applications
                    for export licenses falsely indicating France as the ultimate destination.
                    Licenses will not be issued. There is no foundation for the statement that this
                    Government has approved the proposed transaction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
